President Trump visited Rode's Camera Shop in Kenosha, Wisconsin, which is one of the oldest stores in the nation. The store owner expressed gratitude for the federal troops that were sent to help calm the situation during the recent unrest. President Trump mentioned that if they had been called one day earlier, they could have saved the store from destruction. He criticized governors and mayors for not calling for federal assistance sooner. The President also mentioned the situation in Portland and Minneapolis, saying that the federal government could have resolved the unrest quickly if called upon. President Trump thanked Bill Barr and Chad, and stated that they would have meetings and a roundtable discussion with the store owners to discuss assistance and rebuilding efforts.